Data Wrangling

jails <- jails %>%
  filter(State == "Louisiana")
jails <- jails %>%
  mutate(County_Profile = County_Profile * 100)
jails <- jails %>%
  mutate(obs_num = c(1:55)) 
lajails$county_name = str_replace(lajails$county_name, " Parish", "")
jails$County = as.character(jails$County)
jails$CountyState = as.character(jails$CountyState)
jails[27,3] <- "La Salle"
jails[27,2] <- "La Salle, Louisiana"
lajails$county_name = as.factor(lajails$county_name)

jails <- left_join(jails, lajails, by = c("County" = "county_name"))
## Warning: Column `County`/`county_name` joining character vector and factor,
## coercing into character vector
jails$private_jail_flag = as.factor(jails$private_jail_flag)
jails <- jails %>%
  mutate(pctblackjail = (black_jail_pop)/(total_jail_pop) * 100) %>%
  mutate(pctlatinxjail = (latinx_jail_pop)/(total_jail_pop) * 100) %>%
  mutate(pctwhitejail = (white_jail_pop)/(total_jail_pop) * 100) %>%
  mutate(pctpretrial = (total_jail_pretrial)/(total_jail_pop) * 100) %>%
  mutate(pctprison = (total_jail_from_prison)/(total_jail_pop) * 100) %>%
  mutate(pctjailfromother = (total_jail_from_other_jail)/(total_jail_pop) * 100) %>%
  mutate(pctcapacity = (jail_rated_capacity)/(total_jail_pop) * 100)

Model Fitting

model <- glm(ab_avg ~ County_Profile +
                Jurisdiction_Profile + COVID.19_Deaths + urbanicity + private_jail_flag + pctblackjail + pctlatinxjail + pctwhitejail + pctpretrial + pctprison + pctjailfromother + pctcapacity , data = jails)

model_aic <- step(model, direction = "backward", trace=FALSE) 

tidy(model_aic) %>%
  select(term, estimate, p.value)
## # A tibble: 8 x 3
##   term                estimate p.value
##   <chr>                  <dbl>   <dbl>
## 1 (Intercept)           0.990  0.197  
## 2 County_Profile        0.0144 0.0697 
## 3 urbanicitysmall/mid  -0.0399 0.757  
## 4 urbanicitysuburban   -0.384  0.0734 
## 5 urbanicityurban       0.828  0.125  
## 6 private_jail_flag1    0.395  0.0684 
## 7 pctblackjail         -0.0113 0.143  
## 8 pctwhitejail         -0.0242 0.00883
model_aug <- augment(model_aic) %>%
  mutate(obs_num = row_number())
leverage_threshold <- 2*(8 + 1)/nrow(model_aug)

high_leverage <- model_aug %>%
  mutate(high_lev = .hat > leverage_threshold) %>%
  select(high_lev, obs_num)

high_leverage %>%
  filter(high_lev == TRUE)
## # A tibble: 1 x 2
##   high_lev obs_num
##   <lgl>      <int>
## 1 TRUE          32

Morehouse county has a large percent reduction in prison population.

ggplot(data = model_aug, aes(x = obs_num, y = .std.resid)) +
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

model_aug %>%
  summarise(min = min(.std.resid, na.rm = TRUE),

            median = median(.std.resid, na.rm = TRUE))

  mutate(high_sd = abs(.std.resid) > 2) %>%
  select(obs_num, high_sd)

high_sdresid %>%
  filter(high_sd == TRUE)

grps <- 10
brks <- quantile(model_aug$.resid, 0:(grps-1)/(grps-1), na.rm=TRUE, 
                 names = FALSE)

  select(.resid, obs_num)

jails <- left_join(jails, residuals, by = c("obs_num" = "obs_num"))

  geom_col(aes(x = `Above Average Decrease in Prisoners`, y= `Percent of Prisoners White`), data = averages, fill = c("red", "skyblue")) 

plotbiv <- jails %>%
  arrange(County_Profile) %>%
  arrange(ab_avg) %>%
  mutate(obs_num = c(1:55))

ggplot () +
